narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: difficult class that you need to review for and follow closely; makes you work and truly learn the language
Take this course with Oscar! He is the best. The class is interesting as well and the material is applicable.

I would recommend this class to someone if, like me, they honestly want to improve their admittedly rudimentary Spanish skills. It was very formulaic, but definitely instilled in me a better understanding of the Spanish language. The homework was never too bad and the Professors are all pretty good.
Take it, you are going to need the language credit anyways.
More fast-paced than L1, its not bad if you can stay with it.
Harder than L1 so get ready
Yes, you learn a lot of spanish
Well, if you want Yale credit you need to do L2

Small sections capped at 16. I was placed into L2 after 3 years of Spanish in high school and felt that my oral ability was equal to my classmates, but my knowledge of grammar, and perhaps some vocab, was more appropriate to a higher level.
